SIMPLE: northing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Northing
<hw>North"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Surv. &
Navigation)</fld> <def>Distance northward from any point of departure or
of reckoning, measured on a meridian; -- opposed to
<ant>southing</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The distance of any heavenly
body from the equator northward; north declination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>northland</ent>⟦br⟧
